                            <comment id="465616" author="adilger" created="Thu, 31 Jul 2025 07:34:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Alexander, while it is true that there were some failures before the &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18218&quot; title=&quot;Performance impact on MDT performance with changelogs enabled&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18218&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18218&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch landed, the majority of those failures appear to be related to a regression in a specific patch, or they have different error symptoms.  The &quot;&lt;tt&gt;creation thread is running. Is changelog reader stuck&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; message only started being it frequently on 2025-05-06 on master-next and then on master after 2025-05-09 after the patch landed.   It is possible that this might be caused by a different patch in that group of landings, but &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18218&quot; title=&quot;Performance impact on MDT performance with changelogs enabled&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18218&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18218&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; seemed the most likely.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
